  <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 16px; color: var(--beeswax); line-height: 1.7;">The Holy Spirit is not a concept to be understood but a presence to be experienced. The next time you are in a Byzantine church, watch for the <em>epiklesis</em> — the moment when the priest calls down the Holy Spirit upon the gifts. That is the Spirit at work. In the meantime, begin each morning with the prayer: <em>O Heavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, who art everywhere present and fillest all things, Treasury of good things and Giver of life: come and dwell in us.</em></p>
